article.headline: Northeastern 76, Hartford 59
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea scored 23 points on Wednesday night as Northeastern survived a sluggish start to beat Hartford 76-59. The Huskies (10-6, 4-1 America East) missed their first six field goals and trailed 10-2 nearly five minutes into the first half. But after the teams traded baskets, Northeastern went on a 14-0 run to take an 18-12 lead. The Hawks (4-8, 0-4) tied the game at 20-20 at the midway point of the half, but Northeastern pulled away and used a 13-2 run for a 42-31 halftime lead. Playing without leading scorer Marcus Barnes (19.8 ppg), who was serving the first game of a two-game suspension for his role in an on-court altercation against Vermont last week, Northeastern had little trouble scoring, with four players in double digits. Javorie Wilson scored 11 first-half points and finished with 14, while Jesse Dunn had 11 and Davis added 10. Sylbrin Robinson had a game-high 11 rebounds. Ryan Stys scored 20 points to lead Hartford while Aaron Cook added 12. The Hawks struggled from the field, hitting just 37 percent of their shots, including 4 of 26 3-pointers.
